Old Mutual Zimbabwe Unit Approves Plan to Meet Ownership Law, Newsday Says

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-09-09T07:39:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/old-mutual-zimbabwe-unit-approves-plan-to-meet-ownership-law-newsday-says.html
Old Mutual Plc (OML) ’s  Zimbabwe  insurance
unit approved a plan to meet a requirement for foreign companies
to sell a majority stake to black Zimbabweans, Newsday reported,
citing Chief Executive Officer Luke Ngwerume.  Old Mutual Zimbabwe Ltd. is negotiating with Zimbabwe’s
indigenization ministry after being given seven days to show how
it will meet the law, the Harare-based newspaper said on its
website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
